
how to create a virtual environment for python

1. sudo apt-get install python3-pip

2. to install virtual env -  sudo pip3 install virtualenv

3. to create a virtual env - virtualenv myvenv
   you can also create virtualenv using Python3 -
   virtualenv -p python3 myvenv

4. then change to that directory - cd myvenv

5. to activate the virtual environment - source bin/activate

6. then install all the frameworks you want to
   install here

7. if you want to come out of the virtual environment
   just type - deactivate